Product Id: National Population Health Survey: Household Component, Cross-sectional
Source: Statistics Canada, National Population Health Survey, 1994/95, 1996/97 and 1998/99, cross sectional sample, health file
Population aged 12 and over who report that they have been diagnosed by a health professional as having diabetes.  These data are not available for age 11 and under.
Bootstrapping techniques were used to produce the coefficient of variation (CV) and 95% confidence intervals (CIs).
Data with a coefficient of variation (CV) from 16.6% to 33.3% are identified by an (E) and should be interpreted with caution.
Data with a coefficient of variation (CV) greater than 33.3% were suppressed (F) due to extreme sampling variability.

The cross-sectional component of the National Population Health Survey (NPHS) has been taken over by the Canadian Community Health Survey (CCHS). The table (104-0011) was archived. More recent data are in table (105-0011).
